/-- EBHFM — Rudin 1987 Chs. 18-20 (breach_candidate, D1, opus-ahn max).
    Elementary Banach algebras + holomorphic Fourier transforms + Mergelyan:
    Ch. 18 (Banach algebras): Gelfand spectrum + maximal-ideal space; Gelfand
    transform; Wiener tauberian theorem (1/f Wiener algebra membership).
    Ch. 19 (Holomorphic Fourier): Paley-Wiener theorem (1934): f ∈ L²(ℝ)
    extends to entire function of exponential type ≤ A iff supp f̂ ⊆ [-A, A].
    Denjoy-Carleman quasi-analyticity (1921/1926): a class C{M_n} of smooth
    functions is quasi-analytic iff ∑ 1/M_n^{*1/n} = ∞ (where M_n^* is the
    log-convex regularization).
    Ch. 20 (Mergelyan 1951): if K ⊂ ℂ is compact with ℂ \ K connected and
    f ∈ C(K) is holomorphic in the interior of K, then f is uniformly
    approximable on K by polynomials.
    Citation: S. Banach 1932 *Théorie des opérations linéaires*; I. M. Gelfand
    1941 *Normierte Ringe* Mat. Sbornik 9; R. E. A. C. Paley + N. Wiener 1934
    *Fourier Transforms in the Complex Domain* AMS Coll. XIX; A. Denjoy 1921
    C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris 173; T. Carleman 1926 *Les fonctions quasi-
    analytiques*; S. N. Mergelyan 1951 Dokl. Akad. Nauk SSSR 78; Rudin 1987
    Chs. 18-20. -/
